                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Hmm, so you're suggesting that a typical pull of a room might be one red, one high blue, one low blue, and two greens?
<br />

<br />
That would be very interesting.  There's something big enough to challenge the tank (or rather the cleric trying to heal him), but also some crowd control on the side.  To a lower level group it would actually look like four blues and a high red so they'd get more xp, and to a higher level group it would look like one yellow, one blue, and three greens, so they'd get less xp.
<br />

<br />
The mobs might have to be linked somehow, to prevent monks from using FD to pull the greens out first, which spoils the whole scheme.  Also they'd need to respawn all at once else campers could quickly pull singles as they respawned.  In some cases they might need to be uncharmable too (lest a dire charm prevent them from ever respawning at all).
<br />

<br />
It would be interesting to see if people would still skip enchanters and just use pets to offtank the greens, or maybe use paladins and rangers to offtank the blues.  But that's not all bad... that's what groups are supposed to do when they don't have an enchanter.  Even wizards might get more variety... in groups with poor crowd control they might be asked to finish off the greens fast, but in other groups they'd be asked to concentrate on the red con.</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
                        </tr>
                </table></td>
        </tr>
