<br />

<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">It would be interesting to see if people would still skip enchanters and just use pets to offtank the greens, or maybe use paladins and rangers to offtank the blues. But that's not all bad... that's what groups are supposed to do when they don't have an enchanter. Even wizards might get more variety... in groups with poor crowd control they might be asked to finish off the greens fast, but in other groups they'd be asked to concentrate on the red con.</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
The ratio between mob DPS and mob HPs should tell the wizard who to focus on blowing up.
<br />

<br />
72: 800 DPS/35,000 hps = 23 DPS/1k HPs
<br />
66: 500 DPS/28,000 hps = 18 DPS/1k HPs
<br />
62: 250 DPS/18,000 hps = 14 DPS/1k HPs
<br />

<br />
Which says the wizard should, if you get single pulls, nuke mainly on the L 72 mob.  And yes, on multi-pulls, the wizard might want to burn down the weak adds, to prevent cleric-swarming.
<br />

<br />
But, imagine if the zone had L 72 turtles and L 68 spiders with the following stats:
<br />
72: 700 DPS, 60,000 hps = 12 DPS/1 k HPs
<br />
68: 600 DPS, 20,000 hps = 30 DPS/1 k HPs
<br />
In this zone, wizards would burn down the spiders, and let the 'constant DPS people' work on the Turtles.</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
