                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Crowd Control:
<br />

<br />
You have something that I view the enchanter class as being built to do, and you've torn it down into nothing.  That's like if all mobs had 1 hit point and rampage/ae nukes were taken out of the game, how would that affect a rogue?  It would do less damage to the rogue as a class than this has to enchanters because the rogue could still do dps.  Sure since it just takes 1 hit to kill everything he'd be on par with warriors and monks but he'd still have a purpose.  *Note: do not read this and give all mobs only one hitpoint.  Also don't read this and make mobs in level 70 zones that quad for say 5 damage and are mezzable to make some sort of illusion of needing crowd control.  Use your brain.*  As things stand, I want to see the level 69 mez MUCH easier to obtain since I don't even have it yet as one of the best enchanters in my guild.  I want to see all mezzes in oow as lure based or better due to the fact that when a mob resists people die.  When a mob resists a wizard nuke, the wizard nukes again without any real problem.  oh no we lost 5000 damage, compare that to oh no we lost the cleric.   But me bringing up that example by no means is saying that I am satisfied with the nihilist form of crowd control I see in oow.  I MADE my enchanter, have played him for A YEAR OF /played (yeah yeah I"m a loser) levelling him up worked on him, etc. so that I could do crowd control.  I liked the part of the class that had action, not the buffing people part.  Saying every group shoudln't need an enchanter is fine, but make zones where they do!  I see a lot of zones where you basically need a warrior, paladin, or shadow knight, and who's complaining?!?  Why not zones where you need a bard, enchanter, or monk?  It's ridiculous.
<br />

<br />
Buffs:
<br />

<br />
Now I take it into account that soe has designed zones around people having kei.  Why is it ok that every zone requires kei, but at the same time ok that every zone doesn't require an enchanter?  I know requiring kei is sort of a loose statement, they can't physically require kei to zone in but they are based around it.  This is a double standard.  That is bad.  I do NOT want to see kei time lowered due to the way things are.  I don't want to be bugged for c6 every 5 minutes.  I hate buffing on the whole.  I am firmly against lowering the time kei lasts.  Our haste is only better than shaman hastes, assuming that the melee can reach haste cap on shaman hastes, in that it can increase crits and give more attack.  I don't like the common idea for a cure of this but something else should be done.  What if having an enchanter in the group increase the group's mana regen/attack even more, or something like that if you are going to make buffs a reason to invite people to a group.  Maybe give enchanters a short term buff that stacks with it's current buffs but increases mana regen and attack etc.  However again I would much rather see crowd control brought back into the system.  Buffs are only good up to a certain extent.  They are not a reason to play eq.
<br />

<br />
Debuffs:
<br />

<br />
-I'm changing the format on this one since there are so many issues that if I brought them up more wordily this thread would never end.
<br />
-Casting time on enchanter slow way too long in comparison to other slows.  Come on 6.0 vs. the 1.5 of a shaman's slow?  Yes shaman are better slowers but they're also better healers almost equal dps'ers, better mana regenners (cannibalize) better rooters and thus better groupers (also perhaps better buffers.. champion anyone?).  Also compare enchanter slow to bstlord slow in terms of casting time, remember bsts have pets, and mana regen that you can't get in pok in the form of spiritual radiance type buffs, and the aa ability that regens 250'ish mana/hp a tick for several ticks.  Only slower I'd invite to a group and then say nm we have an enchanter on the way is a bard.  Bards are better at crowd control due to it just being generally 1 add (bards can cast while running, bards have more hp/ac, bards have fading memories)
<br />
-resist debuffs: make tash do more and aggro less.  I don't care if you increase it's cost.  Compare it to malos, it's a sham.  Malos has almost no aggro related to it, so shamans can malos and then slow much easier than enchanters can tash and then slow. Also malos lowers other resistances giving it yet another use. 
<br />
-Slow is the MAIN reason I would see people inviting enchanters to groups in omens of war, and other people who can slow are more solid to have as group members.  At the same time, enchanters are nowhere near as good at slowing (although I consider an enchanter with a serpent of vindication to be better at slowing than a beastlord if he has enough gear to survive an aggro).  Make.  Enchanter.  Slow. Better.  In.  General.
<br />
-Change cripple/weakness line to do something noticeable, like say if a mob is crippled, it deals 5% less damage with each hit than it would otherwise deal.  That would make the spell "useful"  or "worth casting".  
<br />
-sorry this is still so long earlier it was about 5x as long.
<br />

<br />
_____________________________________________________________
<br />

<br />
Extra Category: dps!
<br />

<br />
-Given the lack of crowd control in oow the only thing I do aside from slow mobs and occaisionally buff people is dps!  This is horrible becuase I have the equivalent of cleric nukes and do not charm in oow due to how bad the nerfs are against charm.
<br />
-Increase enchanter nukes (in damage, not casting time/mana cost), but do not consider that the sole solution to the problems encompassing the class.  Consider it a small start.
<br />
-Make mobs that are green con, hit for 200's anyways, don't dual wield, cannot receive weapons/equipment, and are charmable by normal charms.  Make them easy to get to and perhaps non kos.  MAKE THEM NOT AFFECTED BY THE OOW NERF THAT MAKES THEM HIT FOR ABOUT HALF AS MUCH DAMAGE!  This would give enchanters some form of reasonable dps.  
<br />
-I don't really like the way the class is headed by departing from crowd control, but you're taking away what it has as a function in exp groups simply by the environments of the new expansions almost never requiring mez except in raid situations, and you aren't replacing that function in a group with anything.  That's why I made a dps category.  It's my version of a compromise, and it's kind of depressing.  Keep mez for raid situations at least, that would be good.  In fact increase it for raid situations, but if you aren't going to implement situations where crowd control is needed in at least some zones in oow (some fun zones perhaps.   Make a new sebilis =P)</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
                        </tr>
