                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I think the point trying to be made is that bards are supposed to be like "jack-of-all-trades" that are good at many things but great at none.
<br />

<br />
And that the flexibility of having so many different abilities equates to having 1 ability they really excel at.
<br />

<br />
Well, this is a fun idea, but we all know the reality isn't as sweet.
<br />

<br />
I think SoE deliberately made bards great at pulling because they were
<br />
trying to find a niche for bards in grouping.
<br />

<br />
But mostly, there are just so few bards that SoE hasn't felt it all that necessary to fix some of the broken things (like scaling up to ridiculous levels with resists and DSes). 
<br />

<br />
Just some rambling thoughts, sorry if I offended anyone..</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
