                        </tr>
                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody"></span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Manizeh wrote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">Why do you consider Mage to be the primary class for DS? Cause they get unnerfed DS as soon as they get spells? We bards have most of our songs crippled, and they only achive their fullest potential when equiping ourselves with items that HAVE instruments mods, much like nukers really nuke to their potential when they have focis and AAs. And unlike a nuker with no focis, a bard with no instruments sure is half a bard. </td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
Bards are the primary hasters, mana regen buffers, resist buffers, pullers, DS casters, debuffers, mezzers, and snarers in EQ.
<br />

<br />
I'm well aware that Bards are masters of most trades.  =)  Bards gained this position because bard instruments and power growth has been faster than any other 'spell casting' class in the game.
<br />

<br />
In Kunark, bard epic gave 1.8 multiplier to all spells.  Drums (and other instruments) boosted this to 2.4.
<br />

<br />
Now bards can get 4.5 multipliers (including AA).
<br />

<br />
4.5/2.4 = 90% improvement in bard focus abilities.
<br />

<br />
Bard DPS abilities haven't gone up all that much, in the raw spell data.  But non-DPS abilities have.
<br />

<br />
Bard HOS-&gt;OOS is a 50% improvement in resist debuffing.
<br />

<br />
Tash has gone up 20% since Kunark.
<br />
Malo has gone up 22% since Kunark.
<br />
Bard HOS has gone up +185%.
<br />

<br />
Bard 3-song DS is now 51 raw and 220+ focus'd.
<br />
Back in Kunark, it was more like 70.  +214% improvement.
<br />

<br />
Mage DS now is 62
<br />
In Kunark it was 35
<br />
It went up +77%.
<br />

<br />
Basically, bard raw DS amounts in spells went up by the same amount as bard song multipliers.  In a bunch of utility categories, bards are being upgraded at a quadratic rate compared to their competition.  Either the developers are intending bards to become masters of all trades, or they screwed up the math and don't understand bard power growth.</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
                        </tr>
