                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">As always when comparing classes, whining and calling for nerfs, people's claims do not hold to reality
<br />

<br />
Bard max modifiers are 4.2, except Wind Instruments, which while max is also 4.2 there are no items or instruments that will take you pass 4.0 even with all AAs done.
<br />

<br />
Hence the max a bard could provide at level 70 is:
<br />

<br />
171 DS (with Muram, Psalm of Veeshan)
<br />
357 resists (using Psalm of Veeshan)
<br />
65 MR/CR/FR debuff (using HoS)
<br />
109 Heal regen
<br />
23 Mana regen
<br />
57% Slow (with Jam Fest 3 and level 70)
<br />
200ish ATK
<br />

<br />
Realisticaly, NO bard will be smacking a mob with an instrument to provide max brass mod for DS, nor will attack with a drum either for max debuffs.
<br />

<br />
And specially, NO bard will have max mods all across the board, the stuff required is pretty rare, even the small percentage of bards that have access to all max mods will never see them ALL drop, not to mention getting them all.
<br />

<br />
More attainable numbers would be:
<br />

<br />
100-150 DS (and 150 DS assumes Qvic BP or Uqua BP, which falls into the 5% of all bards bracket, so think of it to fall more in the lines of 100-120)
<br />
250-280 Resists (using Psalm of veeshan)
<br />
30-40 MR/CR/FR debuff (using HoS)
<br />
50-70 heal regen
<br />
23 mana regen
<br />
57% slow
<br />
140ish ATK
<br />

<br />
Further debuffing can be attained with dot-of-flavor and Ancient dot, but unless situationally doing it on a raid or event, NO bard will use a dot for debuffing, pretty much ever. Screws with Fading Memories or Mez.
<br />

<br />
Similarly, for practical purposes NO bard will sing anything but PoV and Muram for DS.
<br />

<br />
Unmei, regardless of the numbers of abilities a class can do, mages are not Primary DS class because they have a DS spell, you might think so but they aren't. Druids also have DS, and druids can do anything a bard does but mez, slow and haste, they can however heal (2nd best healer class), buff HPs and mana regen among other buffs, port, evac, dot, nuke...
<br />

<br />
If a mage is Primary DS class with 2nd best DS in game, then they are also Primary nukers. 
<br />

<br />
I have yet to find me an NPC that sells me instrument mods (LDoN don't really count). Before GoD and OOW, you could only get them by way of epic or Elemental+ raids. I don't do bazaar often, never would be a better word, but outside drums saying instruments are ez to get is misleading at best (again before GoD and OOW. God requires top guild raiding as Elemental+ did, and OOW single grouping are pretty hard to get).
<br />

<br />
Chanters do have a case in that a bard makes chanters obsolete, but that is SoE's lame spells and content desing that did it, not bards. However, when people in group ask if a chanter is ok, I never mind, if only for slowing and nuking for 2K with bard song and nuke focis (3.9 crits).
<br />

<br />
