                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody"></span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Manizeh wrote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">As always when comparing classes, whining and calling for nerfs, people's claims do not hold to reality
<br />

<br />
Bard max modifiers are 4.2, except Wind Instruments, which while max is also 4.2 there are no items or instruments that will take you pass 4.0 even with all AAs done.
<br />

<br />
Hence the max a bard could provide at level 70 is:
<br />

<br />
171 DS (with Muram, Psalm of Veeshan)
<br />
357 resists (using Psalm of Veeshan)
<br />
65 MR/CR/FR debuff (using HoS)
<br />
109 Heal regen
<br />
23 Mana regen
<br />
57% Slow (with Jam Fest 3 and level 70)
<br />
200ish ATK
<br />

<br />
Realisticaly, NO bard will be smacking a mob with an instrument to provide max brass mod for DS, nor will attack with a drum either for max debuffs.
<br />
</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
Realistically any bard who's not an idiot can swap in one of the many primary equippable drums in the game to get the best possible mod on HoS at least the first time, to get slow to land.
<br />

<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">
